TestNg:

It is a unit test framework
it is Test Driven Development


Purpose: To design test cases in systematic way 

--It provide different annotations:
--provide html reports
--provide test execution priority/sequences
--Can maintain dependency
--Data Provider

testNG open source free jar files, its Java unit testing framework, we can not use it with any othercoding languages languages

 
 
 Installation:
 1> First install TestNg plugin for eclipse from url: http://beust.com/eclipse
 
 Annotations: As Per preference
 
 Pre-Conditions Annotation
 
 1> @BeforeSuite
 2> @BeforeTest
 3> @BeforeClass 
 4> @BeforeMethods
 
 test case
 4-5>	@Test
 
 Post Conditions Annotations
 
 8> @AfterSuite
 6> @AfterClass
 7> @AfterTest
 5> @AfterMethod
 
 
 pair create with @BeforeMethod, @Test, @AfterMethods 
 
 Skip test using
 
 @Test(enabled=false)
 
 or 
 
 throw new SkipExceptions("message")
 
 
 
 

